## =============================================================================
## Capsule Brain configuration template
## =============================================================================
## Copy this file to `.env` and adjust each value to match your environment.
## `scripts/run_dev.sh` expects these exact keys when it bulk-exports the
## configuration, so keep the variables even if you override the defaults.
## Never commit a populated `.env` file—treat it as local-only secrets.

## =============================================================================
## API server (FastAPI served by uvicorn)
## =============================================================================
## `CB_API_HOST` feeds both the Kubernetes/Docker manifests in `deploy/` and
## `scripts/run_dev.sh`. The dev launcher binds to `0.0.0.0` regardless, but
## customizing the value keeps your generated `.env` aligned with the target
## topology. `CB_API_PORT` is read by uvicorn and the dev script when it builds
## the service URL.
CB_API_HOST=0.0.0.0
CB_API_PORT=8000

## =============================================================================
## Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS)
## =============================================================================
## Provide a comma-separated list of allowed browser origins with no spaces so
## FastAPI parses each value correctly. Include both `localhost` and `127.0.0.1`
## during local work to avoid confusing preflight failures when browsers mix
## DNS and loopback addresses.
ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000,http://localhost:8000,http://127.0.0.1:8000

## =============================================================================
## Authentication secrets for admin interfaces (Capsule Brain + overseer)
## =============================================================================
## These values gate administrative access for both the FastAPI admin surface
## and the overseer service in `teacher/`. Generate fresh secrets before
## deploying anywhere other than your local machine, and rotate them regularly
## in production scripts.
ADMIN_TOKEN=your_admin_token_here
ADMIN_API_KEY=your_admin_api_key_here

## =============================================================================
## Large language model (LLM) provider API keys
## =============================================================================
## Set at least one provider. Leave unused providers commented out so the dev
## script does not export empty values into your shell. When using Azure OpenAI
## configure the Azure deployment-specific variables separately in `deploy/`
## manifests or your hosting platform.
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_key_here
# COHERE_API_KEY=your_cohere_key_here
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_azure_openai_api_key_here

## =============================================================================
## Telemetry and monitoring exporters
## =============================================================================
## Capsule Brain emits OpenTelemetry spans and metrics by default. Flip the
## flag below to `false` if you prefer to disable telemetry locally. The value
## is consumed by both the FastAPI app and `scripts/run_dev.sh`, which forwards
## it to the background services it launches.
TELEMETRY_ENABLE=true

## =============================================================================
## Testing helpers
## =============================================================================
## Integration tests and smoke scripts use this base URL when targeting the
## API. Adjust the scheme, host, or port if your deployment differs from the
## FastAPI defaults above so automated checks point at the correct server.
CB_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000

## =============================================================================
## Legacy launcher / CLI compatibility
## =============================================================================
## The legacy Python entry points (`launch_capsule_brain.py` and
## `run_overseer.py`) still read the generic `HOST` and `PORT` variables
## directly. Keep these synchronized with the `CB_API_*` values until the CLI is
## fully migrated.
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8000

## =============================================================================
## TLS reverse proxy guidance
## =============================================================================
## Uncomment this when running Capsule Brain behind a TLS-enabled reverse proxy
## (for example, the docker-compose stack in `docker-compose.reverse-proxy.yml`)
## and set it to the externally visible domain so cookies and redirects use the
## correct host.
# CB_DOMAIN=cb.example.com
